# Line-ending policy for the repository.
#
# Every text file is stored with LF in Git. Pinning the working tree to LF as
# well (eol=lf) means no checkout-time conversion happens, which silences the
# "LF will be replaced by CRLF the next time Git touches it" warnings that
# core.autocrlf=true emits on Windows. The toolchain here (Node, Rust, Python)
# is happy with LF on every platform.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets — Git must never apply line-ending or text filters to these.
*.ico  binary
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif  binary
*.webp binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf  binary
*.otf  binary
*.zip  binary
*.gz   binary
*.exe  binary
*.dll  binary
*.msi  binary
